# Alpiq Release Maven Plugin

The **Alpiq Release Maven Plugin** automates the generation of Alpiq deployment artifacts.

It provides two Maven goals:

- **create-postman** : Generate the `alpiq-scripts.json` collection from Java REST APIs.
- **build-release** : Build a complete B2B/B2C release from the release-notes directory.

---

# Features

## Create Postman

Automatically scans Java REST APIs and generates the Postman collection used to deploy Alpiq scripts.

Generated file:

```
target/generated-postman/
└── alpiq-scripts/
    └── alpiq-scripts.json
```

The scan can be:

- complete
- filtered using Git history
- include local uncommitted scripts

---

## Build Release

Builds the release packages for B2B and B2C environments.

The plugin automatically merges:

```
0-both
+
1-b2c

or

0-both
+
2-b2b
```

and generates the deployment packages.

---

# Plugin Configuration

```xml
<plugin>
    <groupId>com.alpiq.maven</groupId>
    <artifactId>alpiq-release-maven-plugin</artifactId>
    <version>1.0.0</version>

    <configuration>

        <!-- Java source directory -->
        <inputDir>${project.basedir}/src/main/java</inputDir>

        <!-- Git repository containing Java scripts -->
        <scriptsModulePath>${project.basedir}</scriptsModulePath>

        <!-- Release notes root directory -->
        <releaseNotesDir>${project.basedir}/release-notes</releaseNotesDir>

        <!-- Output directory -->
        <outputDir>${project.build.directory}</outputDir>

        <!-- Scan only modified scripts -->
        <modifiedLastDays>30</modifiedLastDays>

        <!-- Include local uncommitted scripts -->
        <withLocalScript>true</withLocalScript>

    </configuration>
</plugin>
```

---

# Goal : create-postman

Generate the Postman collection.

```
mvn alpiq:create-postman
```

This command scans every REST API.

---

## Generate only modified scripts

```
mvn alpiq:create-postman \
    -DmodifiedLastDays=30
```

The plugin scans only Java files modified during the last 30 days.

---

## Include local scripts

```
mvn alpiq:create-postman \
    -DmodifiedLastDays=30 \
    -DwithLocalScript=true
```

The plugin scans:

- committed Java files modified during the last 30 days
- modified local Java files
- newly created Java files (Git status)

---

# Goal : build-release

```
mvn alpiq:build-release \
    -DreleaseVersion=26.06.01
```

