# SQL Merge

Every SQL script is merged into a single file.

Each original file name is preserved as a comment.

Example:

```sql
/******************************************************************************
 * File : 001_create_customer.sql
 ******************************************************************************/

CREATE TABLE CUSTOMER (...);

/******************************************************************************
 * File : 002_add_contract.sql
 ******************************************************************************/

ALTER TABLE CONTRACT (...);
```

---

# Recommended Workflow

## 1 - Compile

```
mvn clean install
```

---

## 2 - Generate Postman scripts

```
mvn alpiq:create-postman \
    -DmodifiedLastDays=30 \
    -DwithLocalScript=true
```

Generates:

```
target/generated-postman/
└── alpiq-scripts/
    └── alpiq-scripts.json
```

---

## 3 - Prepare Release Notes

```
release-notes/
└──26.06.01/
    ├──0-both/
    ├──1-b2c/
    └──2-b2b/
```

---

## 4 - Build Release

```
mvn alpiq:build-release \
    -DreleaseVersion=26.06.01
```

